"7\bYou Can't Kill Me, I Quit (\iSeifer Rule\i)\b\n
"tThe good guys never seem to get the hang of actually arresting or killing the bad guys. Minor villains are always permitted to go free so they can rest up and menace you again later -- sometimes five minutes later. Knowing this rule, you can deduce that if you do manage to kill (\ior force the surrender of\i) a bad guy, you must be getting near the end of the game.\n\n
