"C\bIf You Meet The Buddha In A Random Encounter, Kill Him!\b\n
"When you're out wandering around the world, you must kill everything you meet. People, animals, plants, insects, fire hydrants, small cottages, anything and everything is just plain out to get you. It may be because of your rampant kleptomania (\isee Garrett's Principle.\i)\n\n
